I love the environment, the wait staff, the wine selection and the fish is the best that Boise has to offer.

caption: This is by far one of my families favorite sushi places! The atmosphere is incredible and we are never disappointed with the service. We recently tried some new entrees, recommended by our server, Chase. These too did not disappoint. 10/10. If you are a seafood lover you must give this place a try!

Both locations have quality food but the downtown Boise location is by far the most beautiful.

We had date night there during Restaurant Week and everything was outstanding! I’ve been in the service industry for going on 20 years, and I can’t even remember the last time I made it through the experience without a single complaint. It was a busy Friday night, BSU was playing BYU, so naturally it was even busier. We were running late for our reservation, my fault, we called and they didn’t make a big deal about it to start. Everything we ordered from the lobster stuffed avocado and Mojo roll to the warm bread pudding with ice cream was outstanding! But the main reason for this review is because of the service!!!! Our server was this amazing young man that had started out as a Sous chef or prep cook (bonus points for knowing the items from start to finish), he had great recommendations (the bread pudding is outta this world), and at the conclusion of the meal we had great conversation (I’m so sorry I don’t remember your name) It is exceptionally difficult to find a place without standing food and over the top service!!! Well done guys!!! I would definitely go check out Lucky fins, I promise you won’t regret it.

Lucky Fin's (Boise Centre on the Grove) is a great place to eat. It gets very busy at times, but that comes with good food in a good location. The patio in the summer looking onto the fountain is one of the best al fresco spots in all of Boise's downtown. They have a variety of nuevo seafood dishes, with their own takes on some seafood classics. The sushi is great even though it is not their raison de etre. The staff is attentive and even with pandemic measures in place it is a great place to hit up for your seafood cravings in Boise Idaho!

This is one of our top 3 favorite sushi spots in Boise and my personal favorite patio.   Parking is a breeze with a parking garage located directly underneath Lucky Fins and no issues on ever finding a spot.   On top of the sushi and the patio, the menu has plenty of non-sushi options.  Fresh seafood, a variety of pastas and some classic items you would see in a menu are what you'll find.   This is a highly agreeable place to eat for a variety of tastes.   My daughter has no problem eating here.  I can't recommend this place enough.   Shout out to the staff for being amazing.  Oh!  Get the "loaded bloody mary".  Just trust me on that one.
